    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Welcome, Anonymous!  I&#8217;m so glad that you found Orangette.  As for this business of sweet potato biscuits with ham, my family has always used one particular spread, and nothing else.  It&#8217;s a type of mustard called Honeycup Uniquely Sharp Mustard.  You can often find it in gourmet shops and delis, and I think that Whole Foods might carry it as well, if you have one of those nearby. It&#8217;s a somewhat creamy mustard that includes brown sugar, honey, and various spices, which makes it sweet, spicy, and delicious.  That, plus some good ham and a good sweet potato biscuit, is <>heaven<>.  I&#8217;m not sure if it&#8217;s the flavor you have in mind, but you might give it a try&#8230;</p>
    </div>

